properties.bio:
Entrepreneur, angel investor, founder of Gust, NY Angels, US Real Estate Market, Associate Founder Singularity University, NYT bestselling author.

I am the founder and Executive Chairman of Gust; founder and CEO of the US Real Estate Market; founder and Chairman Emeritus of New York Angels; Managing Principal of Rose Tech Ventures; a Partner in True Global Ventures, a founding member of Space Angels; and author of the New York Times bestsellers The Startup Checklist: 25 Steps to a Scalable, High-Growth Business and Angel Investing: The Gust Guide to Making Money & Having Fun Investing in Startups; 

I founded the Finance, Entrepreneurship and Economics track at Singularity University, of which I am an Associate Founder.

Ive been involved in the development of the Silicon Alley technology community in New York for many decades, including working with online data services in the 1970s, founding an early personal computer training company in the 1980s, a wireless data information network in the 1990s, an international angel investing platform in the 2000s and an institutional capital markets platform for commercial real estate in the 2020s.

Startups that I seed-funded have been acquired by Google, Amazon, Facebook, Uber, Intel, Oracle, S&P Global, Kodak, CBS, and other public companies.

I co-founded the AREA real estate technology accelerator in New York City, was Mentor of the Year at NYU Stern Business School, and was nicknamed The Pitch Coach by BusinessWeek (you may have come across my TED video on the subject, which has had well over a million views to date).

Before entering the technology field, I had prior careers in real estate and government. My avocation is the archaic art and craft of letterpress printing, and I am a book collector with an extensive collection on the history of the book.

Im a native New Yorker; a graduate of the New York City public schools and Horace Mann High School. I received my BA in Urban Affairs from Yale, an MBA in Finance from Columbia Business School, and an honorary Doctor of Engineering degree from Stevens Institute of Technology. I am an Associate Fellow of Pierson College at Yale and a member of the Entrepreneurship Advisory Boards of Columbia Business School and the Yale Entrepreneurial Institute.

I am a Holistic Practitioner, with 30+ years of experience, specializing in somatic and energy healing to harmonize the body, mind and spirit through breathing techniques, chakra work, reflexology, health counseling and consultations.

I mediate differences between the overwhelmed parents and their children when they are at odds with each other.

I help people get to the zone that leads them to places they have always hoped for in their lives.
 
I have been a judge, investigator, and administrative hearing officer for over two decades.  As a judge in Haiti, I presided over civil and criminal cases.  As a consultant for the US Department of Justice, I assisted in formulating and implementing strategies and rules for overall reform of the Haitian judicial system. 

For fourteen years, I worked as an Administrative Law Judge, adjudicating suspension cases brought against students in the public schools of NYC by the Superintendent.  

I built a seafood business in Haiti which ended up supplying leading restaurants, hotels and the general population. We also exported lobster and conch to Europe and the USA.

I have dabbled in real estate and own properties in NYC and Haiti.

I am fluent in Haitian Creole, French and Spanish. I have been a radio and TV co-host on community affairs and I have co-authored a book on couples relationships with my husband, and Ive published several articles on SelfGrowth.com.  I have a Master of Law (LLM) from George Washington University and a law degree from Faculte de Droit et des Sciences Economiques in Haiti.  I am a member of the State Bar of New York.

I am a mother of 3 men and grandmother of 6.

In other words, I am an alternative health practitioner masquerading as an attorney, business person and real estate enthusiast in real life.

I welcome the opportunity to be of service.

Lecturer in Reproductive and Molecular Genetics working on CRISPR genome editing at University College London, UK. 

CEO and Founder of Hertility Health @hertility_health 

Current Director for the MSc in Reproductive Science and Womens Health at University College London. 

Hertility Health is an innovative biotech company on a mission to give women the ability to track their fertility and reproductive health. Research is the focus of our initiative through a machine-learning driven healthcare solution which integrates both a symptom checker and biomarker testing, delivered to the door. 
We tailor each womans individual hormone panel by taking into account her reproductive and medical history. We, therefore, ensure that testing, route-to-diagnosis and care is accurate, accessible and affordable. 
We are excited to be the first to offer a 360-degree view into each individual womans health and will build on this exponentially to have an inclusive, comprehensive dataset of female pathologies, genetics and biomarkers, enabling ever-learning algorithms to aid remote research and innovation for diagnostics and care.
We are using deep learning to identify womens increased risk of fertility deterioration and to prompt clinicians to consider more intensive monitoring and interventions.

With at-home blood test, paired with bespoke testing, actionable advice and a route-to-care, we help women learn more about their own biology and plan accordingly. We are tackling the gender data gap through personalised medicine in reproductive health.

properties.bio:
Hi, I‚Äôm Kay. üëã Previously in Marketing & Growth at Uber and Head of Marketing at a community w/ 3 million entrepreneurs on Instagram. Always believed growth comes from building a purpose-driven brand. Spent 1 year working for myself, now exploring my next move. Open to joining your team. 

At 16 years old, I realized that most people around me didn‚Äôt have a growth mindset due to traditional Belgian narratives we‚Äôre fed as kids. Dreaming big was seen in a negative light and discouraged. It was better to not try than to fail. I took on a job at a local dance school with a goal to save enough money to get out. 

At 21 years old, I used my newly gained digital marketing skills to launch a YouTube channel that caught the eye of a local brand which sent me to Silicon Valley for 3 months.

At 22 years old, I knew that I didn‚Äôt have a visa or a fancy Ivy League education, so breaking into tech was gonna be tricky. That‚Äôs when I heard about this tech startup called Uber. 

I asked people for tours of Uber HQ, Facebook HQ, and secretly left messages on whiteboard to draw attention & hopefully score an interview. Got rejected twice, but tried a third time. 

Spoiler alert: I got the job! That‚Äôs how I landed my job. I bought my one-way ticket to San Francisco to join Uber as a social media manager.

That kickstarted my career in Marketing.

Today, I‚Äôm SO excited to see how much easier it is for anyone with internet to connect with communities of like-minded people and tap into the growth mindset of successful people (e.g. Instagram communities, ClubHouse, Facebook groups, webinars, audiobooks, podcasts, personal brand newsletters).

MY INTENTION:
‚úîÔ∏è Take Clubhouse conversations ‚Äúoffline‚Äù & turn them into a professional circle of friends, collaborators, and mentor/mentee relationships

Entrepreneur, angel investor, founder of Gust, NY Angels, US Real Estate Market, Associate Founder Singularity University, NYT bestselling author.

I am the founder and Executive Chairman of Gust; founder and CEO of the US Real Estate Market; founder and Chairman Emeritus of New York Angels; Managing Principal of Rose Tech Ventures; a Partner in True Global Ventures, a founding member of Space Angels; and author of the New York Times bestsellers The Startup Checklist: 25 Steps to a Scalable, High-Growth Business and Angel Investing: The Gust Guide to Making Money & Having Fun Investing in Startups; 

I founded the Finance, Entrepreneurship and Economics track at Singularity University, of which I am an Associate Founder.

Ive been involved in the development of the Silicon Alley technology community in New York for many decades, including working with online data services in the 1970s, founding an early personal computer training company in the 1980s, a wireless data information network in the 1990s, an international angel investing platform in the 2000s and an institutional capital markets platform for commercial real estate in the 2020s.

Startups that I seed-funded have been acquired by Google, Amazon, Facebook, Uber, Intel, Oracle, S&P Global, Kodak, CBS, and other public companies.

I co-founded the AREA real estate technology accelerator in New York City, was Mentor of the Year at NYU Stern Business School, and was nicknamed The Pitch Coach by BusinessWeek (you may have come across my TED video on the subject, which has had well over a million views to date).

Before entering the technology field, I had prior careers in real estate and government. My avocation is the archaic art and craft of letterpress printing, and I am a book collector with an extensive collection on the history of the book.

Im a native New Yorker; a graduate of the New York City public schools and Horace Mann High School.
